Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve and peel @red onion{1}(peeled and divided); thinly slice one half. Finely chop remaining onion until you have 2 TBSP. Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Quarter @lime{1}(quartered). Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips.

> For 4 servings: Adjust racks to top and middle positions. Thinly slice whole onion; finely chop a few slices until you have 3 TBSP.

== Pico de Gallo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @red onion{1%half}(finely chopped), tomato, cilantro, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop any large pieces. Wipe out pan.

== Poblano Topping ==

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and poblano. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Return chicken to pan; toss to combine. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook until mixture is thickened and saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If mixture seems dry, add another splash of water.

== Tostadas ==

Meanwhile, drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon}; brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer. Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}.

Toast on top rack of oven, carefully flipping tortillas halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings: Use 2 TBSP oil. Divide between 2 baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks, flipping tortillas and swapping baking sheet positions halfway through toasting.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

== Assembly ==

Divide tortillas between #plates{}; evenly sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Top with chicken mixture, pico de gallo, and @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}. Drizzle with @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.